<li> Please accept my sincere condolences. Is there anything I can do to help during this time of grief?</li>
<li> I'm here for you.  Don't hesitate to call if you need someone to talk to or run errands.</li>
<li> Sending you heartfelt condolences. Please let me know if I can assist with anything practical, like childcare or household tasks.</li>
<li> My thoughts are with you.  I'm happy to help with whatever you need in the coming weeks.</li>
<li> With deepest sympathy. Please don't hesitate to reach out if you need any support.</li>
<li> I am so sorry for your loss. Let me know how I can lend a hand during this time.</li>
<li> Accepting my deepest condolences. If there's anything at all I can do, please don't hesitate to ask.</li>
<li> So very sorry for your loss.  Please don't hesitate to call upon me for any assistance.</li>
<li> Thinking of you all.  Let me know if you need any help with arrangements or anything else.</li>
<li> With deepest sympathy. I'm here to help in any way I can.</li>
<li> My heartfelt condolences to you and your family. Please don't hesitate to ask for help with anything you might need.</li>
<li> I'm so very sorry for your loss.  If there's anything practical I can help with, please let me know.</li>
<li> Sending love and support. Please know I'm here to help in any way possible.</li>
<li> Deepest condolences.  Let me know if you need anything at all – big or small.</li>
    
    
    
